doc.after: Clinton's job approval rating fluctuated in the 40s and 50s throughout his first term. In his second term, his rating consistently ranged from the high-50s to the high-60s.[164] After his impeachment proceedings in 1998 and 1999, Clinton's rating reached its highest point.[165] According to a poll conducted by CBS in conjunction with the New York Times, he finished with an approval rating of 68Â percent, which matched those of Ronald Reagan and Franklin D. Roosevelt as the highest ratings for departing presidents in the modern era.[166]
